      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/sqa-mrl2-criteria",
      "rationale": "The CFD solver (ANSYS Fluent 2022R2) is a commercially validated code with documented V&V history. Version control, change logs, and regression test suite (150+ test cases) are maintained under ISO 9001 QMS. SQA activities satisfy MRL 2 requirements per ASME V&V 40 Table 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/ncv-mrl2-criteria",
      "rationale": "Benchmark verification cases including lid-driven cavity, backward-facing step, and rotating channel flow were executed against published analytical and numerical reference solutions. All residuals converged below 1e-6; benchmark errors within 1.5% of reference values. Code verification documented in solver QA report QA-2022-CFD-007."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/disc-error-mrl2-criteria",
      "rationale": "Grid convergence index (GCI) study performed on three systematically refined meshes (4.1M, 11.3M, 28.7M cells; refinement ratio r=1.4). GCI for NIH quantity of interest: 3.1% on fine mesh. Observed order of convergence p=1.87, consistent with second-order scheme. Discretization error is formally quantified and bounded; achieves Gradation 3 per ASME V&V 40 Table 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/test-conditions-mrl2-criteria",
      "rationale": "In-vitro experiments conducted at matched flow rates (2–6 L/min) and rotational speeds (2500–4500 RPM) corresponding to all five COU operating points. Temperature controlled at 37°C ± 0.5°C. Blood analogue fluid (glycerol-water, viscosity matched to whole blood at 37°C) characterised prior to each test. Test conditions documented in laboratory protocol LP-HEMO-2021-03."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/output-comparison-mrl2-criteria",
      "rationale": "Quantitative comparison metrics include normalised index of hemolysis (NIH), pump head (ΔP), and mid-plane velocity magnitude. Validation metric E = (sim − exp)/exp computed for all quantities. NIH error range −8% to +12%; pump head error range −3.8% to +2.1%. All within pre-specified ±15% acceptance band. Statistical significance assessed via bootstrap confidence intervals."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/qoi-relevance-mrl2-criteria",
      "rationale": "The primary quantity of interest (NIH and derived RH index) directly maps to the regulatory acceptance criterion (RH < 1 relative to predicate device). Secondary QOIs (shear stress distribution, residence time) are mechanistically linked to hemolysis via the power-law damage accumulation model. QOI traceability matrix documented in COU1 assessment report section 4.2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/val-relevance-mrl2-criteria",
      "rationale": "Validation experiments used the same FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry as the COU device model. Operating conditions span the full COU envelope. Blood analogue fluid properties match clinical blood viscosity range. Geometric fidelity confirmed by CMM inspection of test article against CAD nominal dimensions (all features within 0.05 mm). Validation relevance score assessed as High per ASME V&V 40 Table 7."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/solver-error-mrl2-scoped-out",
      "rationale": "At MRL 2, explicit solver error characterisation beyond code verification is not required. Iterative convergence is monitored via residual norms (all below 1e-6) and mass imbalance (below 0.01%). Round-off error is negligible for double-precision arithmetic at operating Reynolds numbers. Scoped out per ASME V&V 40 MRL 2 requirements table; discretization error GCI study subsumes the dominant numerical error contribution."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/use-error-mrl2-scoped-out",
      "rationale": "Simulation workflow executed by two independent analysts following documented simulation protocol SP-CFD-CPB-2021-01. Independent review of mesh, boundary conditions, and post-processing confirmed consistent setup. Use error controls satisfy MRL 2 scope; formal independent V&V audit not required at this risk level. Scoped out per ASME V&V 40 MRL 2 requirements table."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/model-form-mrl2-criteria",
      "rationale": "Reynolds-averaged Navier-Stokes (RANS) with SST k-omega turbulence closure selected based on prior published comparisons for rotary blood pump flows (Hariharan et al. 2011, Fraser et al. 2012). Power-law hemolysis damage accumulation model (Giersiepen 1990, modified Heuser-Opitz) applied with coefficients calibrated to bovine blood. Model form uncertainty estimated via comparison of SST k-omega against LES on a coarse mesh subset; NIH difference 6.8%, within acceptance band."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/model-inputs-mrl2-criteria",
      "rationale": "Boundary conditions (inlet flow rate, outlet pressure, rotational speed) set to match experimental test conditions. Fluid properties (density 1056 kg/m³, dynamic viscosity 3.5 mPa·s) measured for blood analogue at 37°C. Geometric model derived from FDA-released STL with nominal dimensions verified by CMM. Input uncertainty propagated via one-at-a-time sensitivity analysis across ±5% parameter variation; NIH sensitivity coefficients documented in UQ report UQ-2021-HEMO-002."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/test-samples-mrl2-scoped-out",
      "rationale": "At MRL 2 for a Class II device, statistical characterisation of inter-sample manufacturing variability is not required for the credibility assessment. The validation test article was confirmed dimensionally representative of the nominal geometry. Sample-to-sample variability assessment is addressed in the separate design tolerance sensitivity study, which is outside the scope of this COU1 credibility package. Scoped out per ASME V&V 40 MRL 2 requirements table."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/equiv-inputs-mrl2-scoped-out",
      "rationale": "Equivalency of input parameters between validation experiment and COU deployment is established through direct matching of operating conditions and fluid properties (documented in test protocol LP-HEMO-2021-03 and simulation protocol SP-CFD-CPB-2021-01). Formal equivalency metric computation is not required at MRL 2 for this device class. Scoped out per ASME V&V 40 MRL 2 requirements table; equivalency is addressed qualitatively through test condition and model input factor assessments."
    }
  ],
  "hasWeakener": [],
  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/morrison-cou1-decision-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment for COU1 (CFD hemolysis prediction for Class II CPB device at MRL 2) is accepted based on the following structured evidence: (1) Seven credibility factors were formally assessed; all achieved levels meet or exceed required levels for MRL 2 per ASME V&V 40 Table 3. (2) Six factors were scoped out with documented justification consistent with MRL 2 requirements. (3) Grid convergence (GCI 3.1%) and model form uncertainty (6.8% NIH difference SST vs LES) are both within the pre-specified ±15% acceptance band. (4) Validation results across all three ValidationResult records demonstrate quantitative agreement with experimental measurements within acceptance criteria for NIH, pump head, and velocity field. (5) Provenance chain is complete: all ValidationResults link to experimental datasets, generating activities, and uncertainty quantification reports. (6) Input uncertainty propagation confirms NIH is not highly sensitive to ±5% parameter variations. (7) The decision consequence is High and model influence is Medium, yielding MRL 2; all assessment activities are commensurate with this risk level. The totality of evidence supports the claim that the CFD model is credible for identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the Class II CPB device within the defined COU envelope.",
    "decidedAt": "2026-04-19T00:00:00Z"
  },
